These rolls are really amazing. I have a few tips to share, though, which is mostly what I love about Epicurious- all the helpful reviews and tips! First, I let the dough rise in the bowl, but instead of baking once that was done, I put the bowl in the fridge. Freshly baked cinnamon rolls were to be a surprise for my son's birthday brunch and I wanted to serve them warm from the oven. That worked well without a problem. I just got them out the next morning, rolled them and placed them in the pan, and let them rise again in a warm oven before baking. Based on reviews I read, I baked them for about 10 minutes longer than the instructions stated. For me, this was not necessary. They may have needed 5 minutes more, but with 10 minutes the end result was that they were a little dry. I may just stick to the recipe this next time and see how that goes. Last, they were not gooey or syrupy at all. That seems like an easy fix next time, though. I plan to make more of the filling and not baking them as long should help keep everything more moist. My fiance whipped up some orange icing, which he and our boys loved (I prefer more of the cinnamon filling, myself). To conclude, this is a great recipe that produces delicious rolls and seems to withstand tweaking well. I'm making them again (twice in the space of two weeks... tells you they're good) for when our neighbors come for brunch on Sunday :)

