Rating: 3
I changed the recipe to incorporate some of the hints below, so this is "my" version. I don't own a 15X10X2 pan so I used cake pans. 1-1/2 cups warm milk 105-115F 3/4 cup white sugar,1 cup light brown sugar 2 envelopes rapid rise yeast 1 T veg. oil, 1 t vanilla 1 t salt 4 cups all purpose flour, plus more for kneading 2 eggs 2 sticks unsalted butter, room temp 2 T ground cinnamon butter 2 8" round pans, line with parchment, butter parchment Mix yeast in with white sugar, salt, and flour. Add oil and vanilla to warm milk, add half of liquid to flour mix. work quickly into a dough, add remainder of liquid. Add eggs, one at a time. Knead dough until soft and elastic,. Let dough rise in oiled bowl about 15 minutes. In the meantime, beat butter and brown sugar to blend. Roll out of press dough into 16X10" rectangle. Spread with half the butter mixture, trying to leave a plain border 1/2" all the way around. Roll up, pinch seans, cut crosswise as in original. Cut into 12 equal pieces, or as many as will fit in the pans you are using. Spread remaining butter mix on bottom of pan(s). arrange rolls cut side down. Cover and let rise 30 minutes. Bake at 325 for 35-40 minutes. Invert from pan while still hot.

