Rating: 3
Great recipe. Wonderful light texture. I put 1/3 cup sugar into the yeast rather than just 1/4 cup since some folks felt the dough was not sweet enough. Also, I used the tip about lining the baking pan with parchment. It made getting these out of the pan a snap. Once cool, I easily fit them back into the pan to be re-warmed and served in the morning to my bible study class. I would guess the folks who called these dense and chewy either under-kneaded or added to much flour. I used the "dough" setting on my bread machine for the kneading. It kneaded for 20 minutes or so. The dough formed a nice ball, but was pretty sticky to handle. I would have had a hard time kneading it by hand without adding lots more flour. as it was I probably added another half cup - but this is in Houston in the summer where humidity is the name of the game. I was planning to make a cream cheese frosting (a la cinnabons) to pass with the rolls, but these don't need a thing. I also filled half the rolls with raisins and the other half with pecans so as to please those in my family caught up in the nut/no nut schism.

