Rating: 3
For a softer roll, you might try changing the basic ingredients in the recipe to these: l cup scalded milk, cooled to 105-115 degrees; 1/2 cup melted butter; cut the sugar to 1/2 cup; two eggs,room temperature; and use at least 4 cups of flour. For the filling, use only 1/2 cup softened butter, 1 1/2 cups dark brown sugar, mixed with 2 1/2 Tbsp of cinnamon.

